5:
Uh... I'm pretty sure this is where
we're meeting Nate.
18:
Sorry, Alk, but could you lend me a
hand?
22:
Bootleg versions of the prosthetics
you and Themis use have shown up
in an underground gang?
25:
Yup. You should see these bootlegs
too. They make them look like
stereotypical bad guys... It's
embarrassing.
30:
Seriously? Who would use
something like that?
34:
I mean, our gear is chock-full of that
android tech... A lot of people are
willing to pay the price for shiny new
toys.
37:
Not to mention everyone got a
pretty good look at what this tech
can do during that whole thing with
Themis.
40:
Sorry, guys. I wanted to hang out
today, but unfortunately—
45:
Hold that thought, my little hero. I
hereby order you to take a break.
54:
Trivia time! Alk, did you know that
Nate here has been working for
thirty days straight?!
58:
C-come on, it's kinda my fault that
we're in this mess, so of course I've
been—
63:
Stella, you take the left arm, and I'll
take the right.
74:
You know... Heroes never break their
promises.
78:
And you promised to hang out with
us. Therefore you must.
83: Urgh... I mean, that's true, but...
104: Ah! Sorry, did I fall asleep?!
111:
You okay? Maybe we should call it
quits for today.
116:
Urgh... Part of me wants to take you
up on that offer, and the other part
wants to make the most of my day
off...
123:
Can you really not take any time off
right now? Are you that busy?
127:
To be honest, it'd probably be fine.
PBC's recovered pretty quickly from
the hero incident.
129:
And since I was pretty central to
that whole shebang, I haven't
exactly had a lot of jobs coming in.
133:
The problem is that I can't stop
myself from thinking about it when I
do take a break. I just feel like I
should be doing more...
144:
*sigh* If only I was magically
transported to another world. Then
I'd probably get some rest for once.
153:
Ah, right! You're both from another
world!
161:
I mean, I was mostly talking
hypothetically. I can't actually—
166:
Surprise trivia time! Nate's got a lot
of vacation days saved up, and with
all the overtime she's been pulling,
she can take a nice long vacation!
171:
Why are you eavesdropping on our
conversation?!
176:
That's it! I'm blocking you! Don't
peep in on my private time, you
creep!
181:
I can hear you screaming from the
streets. What's going on?
186: Sounds like you need a break.
190: I... didn't expect you to say that.
193:
A personal rule of mine is that I don't
do more work than necessary.
197:
And why are you on another date
with him? I'm free too, you know.
201: How was I supposed to know?!
205:
Pushing yourself to the brink of
death doesn't make you a hero.
208:
If you overdo it, you could lose your
will to fight or forget the reason you
fought in the first place.
211:
Doing so is basically death for us
heroes.
218:
I'm doing plenty of self-reflection.
What about you?
221: Come on, get off my case!
226:
In any case, I understand the
situation. If you're so worried, I'll take
your place at PBC while you're gone.
234:
Well, I am a freelancer, and Lunus
hasn't been giving me much work
lately, so I'm on the lookout for a
new contract.
236:
You don't have a problem with that,
do you, King Johnson?
241:
No problem at all. Although your
employment with us will only be for
a short time. Will that work?
244:
Sure.
There. Now you're out of reasons to
avoid taking a vacation.
249:
Come on... We'll give you three full
meals a day. No more SoyMate!
260:
Argh, fine! I get it! I'll take some time
off!
263:
But in return, I expect you two to do
all sorts of stuff with me, got it?
We're gonna have a blast!
